<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 02 at 3:10PM MDT  by NWS Saltlake</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Garfield and northwestern Kane Counties through 400 PM MDT...
At 309 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 19
miles east of Zion National Park, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Orderville, Glendale, Alton, Long Valley Junction and Mt Carmel.
This includes US Route 89 between mile markers 78 and 109.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
